    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-tikka-masala-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and grate your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-tikka-masala-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>grated onion</strong>,<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-tikka-masala-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, cut your <strong>chicken breast strips</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-tikka-masala-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your<strong> curry powder</strong> and <strong>ground paprika</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Increase the heat to high, add the <strong>chopped chicken</strong> and cook for 3-4 min further or until coated in all of the spices</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-tikka-masala-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, dissolve your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and<strong> honey</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-tikka-masala-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>tomato stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 6-8 min or until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Remove off the heat and stir through your <strong>cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>chicken tikka masala</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-tikka-masala-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>chicken tikka masala</strong> with the <strong>basmati</strong> <strong>rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with your<strong> flaked almonds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
